We started out with rocks. Then we figured out how to sharpen them, and we had hand axes and knives. Then we figured out how to use leverage to increase their force, creating axes and throwing weapons. Then we figured that longer levers made for greater force, creating halberds and swords. Then the Chinese discovered black powder, blah blah, yadda yadda. It's just evolution. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uiamhiro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iamhiro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/1/02 9:03:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10796.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.alphacert.net/~ir0n-bul/Hava.gif height=161 width=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: State of the world</span><hr size=1> There is something ALOT diffrent about cutting someone's head off after battling them for 5min then pointing a gun at someone and shooting.<br>
