You seem to have some misconceptions about war.<br>
<br>
The point of war is to win at as little cost to yourself as possible, and in real life this invariably involves showering the enemy with projectiles from a safe spot, being hidden, attacking civilians to halt industry, etc. Again, it's always been this way. The people who used to march onto an open field in columns stopped fighting that way because they were getting mauled by the guys shooting from the bushes or firing arrows over a hill.<br>
